article.headline: Quinerly, No. 12 West Virginia dispatch High Point 89-54 in Gulf Coast Showcase
article.description: — JJ Quinerly scored 18 of her 22 points in the first half and West Virginia made easy work of High Point, beating the Panthers 89-54 on Friday in an opening-round game of the eight-team Gulf Coast Showcase.
article.linkText: Quinerly, No. 12 West Virginia dispatch High Point 89-54 in Gulf Coast Showcase
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- — JJ Quinerly scored 18 of her 22 points in the first half and West Virginia made easy work of High Point, beating the Panthers 89-54 on Friday in an opening-round game of the eight-team Gulf Coast Showcase. Reserve Jordan Thomas scored 18 points and Jordan Harrison had 13 for West Virginia. Aaliyah Collins scored 11 points for High Point. The 12th-ranked Mountaineers (7-0) advance to face Boise State (7-0) on Saturday. The Broncos beat Illinois State 79-76 on Friday. Quinerly started the game with three layups and a pair of free throws in a little more than three-and-a-half minutes to help West Virginia to a 9-0 lead. Her point total in that stretch topped High Point's overall point total for the quarter as West Virginia led 22-7 after the first. West Virginia used an 8-2 run to start the second quarter to get its first 20-plus point lead of the game with another Quinerly layup and two free throws, a Jordan Thomas layup and a Celia Riviere jumper for a 30-9 lead. The Mountaineers moved their record to 3-0 against the Panthers. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on the AP Top 25 throughout the season. Sign up here.
